    {
      "section_id": "para_37",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "An Act to enable effect to be given to an international agreement for \nthe  establishment  and  operation  of  an  International  Finance \nCorporation, and for purposes connected therewith.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_38",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "[Peninsular Malaysia—30 December 1957; \nSabah and Sarawak—3 November 1966, \nP.U. (A) 404/1966]",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_39",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "Short title and application",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_40",
      "heading": "1.  (1) This Act may be cited as the International Finance Corporation \nAct 1957.",
      "content": "1.  (1) This Act may be cited as the International Finance Corporation \nAct 1957.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_41",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "(2)   This Act shall apply throughout Malaysia.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_42",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "Interpretation",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_43",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "2. (1) In this Act “the Agreement” means any agreement which may \nbe signed and accepted on behalf of the Government of Malaysia in \npursuance of Articles approved on the eleventh day of April 1955, by \nthe  executive  directors  of  the  International  Bank  for  Reconstruction \nand Development and providing for the establishment and operation  \nof  an  international  body  to  be  called  “the  International  Finance \nCorporation”  (copies  of  which  Articles,  and  of  an  explanatory \nmemorandum  approved  as  aforesaid,  have  been  laid  before  the \nParliament);  and  “the  Corporation”  means  the  International  Finance \nCorporation established by the Agreement.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_44",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "6                                   Laws of Malaysia                              ACT 439",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_45",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "(2)",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_46",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "(Omitted).",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_47",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "Financial provisions",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_48",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "3.  (1)  There  shall  be  paid  out  of  the  Consolidated  Fund  all  sums \nrequired  for  the  purpose  of  making  payments  on  behalf  of  the \nGovernment  of  Malaysia  under  paragraph  3(a)  of  Article  II  of  the \nAgreement (which provides for the subscription of shares of stock of \nthe Corporation by the members thereof).",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_49",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "(2)   All sums received by the Government of Malaysia from the \nCorporation  in  pursuance  of  the  Agreement  shall  be  paid  into  the \nConsolidated Fund.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_50",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "Orders for carrying the Agreement into effect",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_51",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "4.   The Yang di-Pertuan Agong may, by order, make such provisions \nas he may consider reasonably necessary for carrying into effect any \nof the provisions of the Agreement relating to the status, immunities \nand  privileges  of  the  Corporation  and  its  governors,  directors, \nalternates, officers and employees.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
